Day 3 Task: Basic Linux Commands

Task: What is the linux command to

To view what's written in a file.
cat a.txt
cat -b: This adds line numbers to non-blank lines
cat -n: This adds line numbers to all lines
cat -s: This squeezes blank lines into one line
cat â€“E: This shows $ at the end of the line


To change and check the access permissions of files.
chmod +rwx (filename to add permissions)
chmod -rwx (directoryname to remove permission)
chmod +x (filename to allow executable permission)
chmod -wx (filename to takeout write and executable program)
ls -l filename

Permission numbers are:

0 = ---

1 = --x

2 = -w-

3 = -wx

4 = r-

5 = r-x

6 = rw-

7 = rwx


To check which commands you have run till now.
history

To remove a directory/ Folder.
rm -r mydir

Text editor

vim
insert mode
normal mode
command mode

search command
grep(similar to crtl+F)


To create a fruits.txt file and to view the content.

Add content in devops.txt (One in each line) - Apple, Mango, Banana, Cherry, Kiwi, Orange, Guava.
??

To Show only top three fruits from the file.
head -n 3 a.txt

To Show only bottom three fruits from the file.
tail -n 3 a.txt

To create another file Colors.txt and to view the content.

Add content in Colors.txt (One in each line) - Red, Pink, White, Black, Blue, Orange, Purple, Grey.

To find the difference between a.txt and b.txt file.
diff a.txt b.txt
